article.headline: Southern Methodist 68, Prairie View A&M 51
article.story: DALLAS (AP) -- Donatas Rackauskas hit 10-of-12 shots from the field for a career-high 21 points in SMU's 68-51 win over Prairie View A&M on Wednesday night. Ike Ofoegbu added 14 points and grabbed a team-high 10 rebounds for the Mustangs (7-1). Devon Pearson had 10 points and seven rebounds while Jon Killen led the team with seven assists. The Panthers (1-7) trailed 32-25 at the break. But the Mustangs hit almost 64 percent of their second-half shots compared to the Panthers' 32 percent. Ivory McGilvery led Prairie View with 23 points, including five 3-pointers. Andy Genao came off the bench to add 15 points, including four 3-pointers.
